        <num>CCRP 592</num>
        <heading>592.  When jeopardy begins</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 592.  When jeopardy begins
When a defendant pleads not guilty and is tried by jury, jeopardy begins when the jury panel is sworn pursuant to Article 790.  When a defendant pleads not guilty, and is tried without a jury, jeopardy begins when the first witness is sworn at the trial on the merits.  When a defendant pleads guilty, jeopardy begins when a valid sentence is imposed.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
